  "alternateName": ["NOMI", "Non-Occlusive Mesenteric Infarction", "Low-Flow Mesenteric Ischemia"],
  "description": "Mesenteric ischemia occurring without arterial or venous occlusion, caused by mesenteric vasospasm in the setting of low cardiac output states. Accounts for 20-30% of acute mesenteric ischemia cases. High mortality due to delayed diagnosis.",
